WEBVTT

00:00:10.720 --> 00:00:11.359
Come in.

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:15.800
Sir.

00:00:16.160 --> 00:00:18.239
Here are the cases you asked for on legal

00:00:18.320 --> 00:00:19.839
foreign fund entry in the past 5 years.

00:00:20.199 --> 00:00:22.039
I only picked ones over 100 million yuan.

00:00:22.559 --> 00:00:25.120
Some via wholly foreign-owned companies,

00:00:25.239 --> 00:00:26.079
some via M&A investments,

00:00:26.079 --> 00:00:28.199
and some via shell company backdoor listings.

00:00:30.239 --> 00:00:32.000
If your client had

00:00:32.280 --> 00:00:34.000
an overseas investment over 100 million,

00:00:34.880 --> 00:00:36.240
and wanted to, within a month,

00:00:36.240 --> 00:00:37.920
enter the market legally and compliantly,

00:00:38.840 --> 00:00:40.079
how would you structure the plan?

00:00:40.600 --> 00:00:42.320
A wholly foreign-owned company

00:00:42.399 --> 00:00:44.479
has too much paperwork and strict reviews.

00:00:45.039 --> 00:00:46.960
Each fund must match a specific business.

00:00:47.079 --> 00:00:47.960
Not flexible enough.

00:00:48.320 --> 00:00:50.280
Finishing in a month is impossible.

00:00:50.840 --> 00:00:52.960
M&A needs a clear target,

00:00:53.240 --> 00:00:54.920
needs Ministry of Commerce approval,

00:00:55.240 --> 00:00:56.759
and involves due diligence.

00:00:57.640 --> 00:00:59.600
That takes at least half a year.

00:01:00.159 --> 00:01:01.679
Backdoor listing seems fast,

00:01:01.759 --> 00:01:03.399
but involves fake capital injections

00:01:03.479 --> 00:01:04.519
and fake transactions.

00:01:04.920 --> 00:01:05.920
Once investigated,

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:08.400
it's treated as false disclosure.

00:01:09.159 --> 00:01:10.959
These cases ended up in the database

00:01:10.959 --> 00:01:13.879
because they all became legal precedents.

00:01:14.359 --> 00:01:18.560
So I think these three standard methods

00:01:19.040 --> 00:01:20.280
are not viable.

00:01:23.239 --> 00:01:24.840
Bro Xiao, I brought someone to see you.

00:01:26.560 --> 00:01:27.239
Who?

00:01:28.200 --> 00:01:29.480
An old friend of mine.

00:01:29.640 --> 00:01:31.640
His family are farmers,

00:01:31.719 --> 00:01:32.920
and he has some spare cash now.

00:01:32.920 --> 00:01:34.840
He wants to ask you about investments.

00:01:35.239 --> 00:01:36.040
A farmer?

00:01:37.760 --> 00:01:39.519
He looks pretty well-off.

00:01:40.920 --> 00:01:42.120
Bro, farming, you know,

00:01:42.200 --> 00:01:44.159
there's more to it than meets the eye.

00:01:44.959 --> 00:01:46.079
You used to farm too?

00:01:48.040 --> 00:01:49.000
My family did.

00:01:50.599 --> 00:01:51.359
Young Master Jin.

00:01:59.040 --> 00:02:00.120
So, Bro Xiao.

00:02:00.239 --> 00:02:00.840
Boss Jin.

00:02:01.159 --> 00:02:01.760
Bro Xiao.

00:02:01.920 --> 00:02:03.200
I've heard so much about you.

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:05.599
A pleasure, truly a pleasure.

00:02:09.199 --> 00:02:10.599
Bro Xiao, don't be so formal.

00:02:10.759 --> 00:02:12.199
One clink of glasses and we're brothers.

00:02:12.319 --> 00:02:13.120
We're all brothers.

00:02:15.159 --> 00:02:16.439
Datou told me

00:02:16.639 --> 00:02:18.319
you wanted to consult me

00:02:18.319 --> 00:02:19.599
about some investment directions.

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:20.680
That's right.

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:22.479
They say Bro Xiao is sharp,

00:02:22.639 --> 00:02:24.000
and knows his way around projects.

00:02:24.280 --> 00:02:25.960
I've got some spare cash lately,

00:02:26.199 --> 00:02:28.120
want to invest in something profitable.

00:02:29.240 --> 00:02:30.280
You flatter me, really.

00:02:31.560 --> 00:02:34.000
You should find a financial advisor.

00:02:34.400 --> 00:02:36.919
Me? I'm okay at handling lawsuits,

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:38.639
but this really isn't my strong suit.

00:02:39.680 --> 00:02:42.159
I don't trust those slippery businessmen.

00:02:42.280 --> 00:02:44.080
When it comes to money, I trust brothers.

00:02:44.520 --> 00:02:46.599
Besides, didn't Bro Xiao

00:02:46.840 --> 00:02:48.520
use to work with Bro Mao?

00:02:51.199 --> 00:02:51.840
All right then.

00:02:52.120 --> 00:02:54.199
So, Boss Jin,

00:02:54.360 --> 00:02:56.520
what kind of projects interest you?

00:02:56.639 --> 00:02:58.960
How much spare cash do you have? We can...

00:02:59.240 --> 00:03:00.439
Sure, we can go over it briefly.

00:03:01.680 --> 00:03:03.319
Money? I've got plenty to spend.

00:03:03.479 --> 00:03:04.240
No need to worry.

00:03:04.560 --> 00:03:05.560
Projects...

00:03:08.719 --> 00:03:09.319
Look,

00:03:09.719 --> 00:03:12.479
the government's been heavily backing

00:03:12.639 --> 00:03:14.000
the aerospace industry.

00:03:14.240 --> 00:03:15.759
So I could invest in

00:03:15.919 --> 00:03:17.439
a private aerospace company.

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:19.520
We'd build rockets,

00:03:20.080 --> 00:03:21.840
and do satellite launches.

00:03:22.080 --> 00:03:24.039
Imagine how much one launch could earn!

00:03:25.919 --> 00:03:26.599
Old Jin,

00:03:26.759 --> 00:03:28.120
You're giving me a massive headache,

00:03:28.280 --> 00:03:29.319
and even I wouldn't dare dream that big.

00:03:30.280 --> 00:03:31.039
Don't be scared.

00:03:32.439 --> 00:03:33.360
How about

00:03:35.159 --> 00:03:36.000
high-speed rail?

00:03:36.560 --> 00:03:38.240
There's a big empty lot in my village.

00:03:38.479 --> 00:03:40.439
We could build a high-speed rail line,

00:03:40.680 --> 00:03:43.039
ship the village's sugarcane and corn

00:03:43.039 --> 00:03:44.159
to the big cities to sell.

00:03:44.319 --> 00:03:46.280
White-collars love local stuff, right?

00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:50.800
Boss Jin,

00:03:51.319 --> 00:03:53.000
the projects you're describing

00:03:53.159 --> 00:03:55.000
are all state-owned projects.

00:03:56.080 --> 00:03:57.280
Private investment

00:03:57.479 --> 00:03:58.360
isn't really realistic.

00:04:00.800 --> 00:04:01.680
What about

00:04:03.919 --> 00:04:05.560
shared e-scooters?

00:04:07.919 --> 00:04:10.120
That's quite a range of options you have.

00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:12.400
The bank recommended some to me,

00:04:12.479 --> 00:04:16.199
talking about new energy policy support.

00:04:17.680 --> 00:04:19.800
They made it sound amazing,

00:04:20.199 --> 00:04:21.480
saying I'd get dividends if I invested.

00:04:21.680 --> 00:04:22.920
But it sounds too good to be true.

00:04:23.160 --> 00:04:24.480
I don't really buy what they're saying.

00:04:24.920 --> 00:04:25.560
Bro Xiao,

00:04:25.839 --> 00:04:26.879
help your little brother out.

00:04:27.199 --> 00:04:27.959
Whichever one's reliable,

00:04:28.160 --> 00:04:29.120
that's the one I'll invest in.

00:04:31.360 --> 00:04:33.720
How about this then.

00:04:34.480 --> 00:04:35.360
Making money takes time,

00:04:35.480 --> 00:04:36.399
so let's not rush it.

00:04:36.759 --> 00:04:37.759
Give me a few days,

00:04:37.920 --> 00:04:38.879
let me do some research.

00:04:39.120 --> 00:04:40.279
Once I have a concrete plan,

00:04:40.399 --> 00:04:41.279
I'll report back to you.

00:04:41.519 --> 00:04:42.040
All right.

00:04:42.199 --> 00:04:43.279
I'll wait to hear from you, Bro Xiao.

00:04:53.120 --> 00:04:53.759
Boss.

00:04:54.519 --> 00:04:56.000
This Xin Youna doesn't trust us.

00:04:57.120 --> 00:04:58.240
So what's our next move?

00:04:59.319 --> 00:05:00.560
The things she won't talk about,

00:05:00.560 --> 00:05:02.160
we'll dig up from someone else.

00:05:03.199 --> 00:05:04.319
The nursing home director,

00:05:04.480 --> 00:05:05.759
the relevant medical staff,

00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:06.879
the money trail.

00:05:07.399 --> 00:05:08.879
We need to investigate this thoroughly.

00:05:09.839 --> 00:05:11.120
Especially Xin Youna.

00:05:11.839 --> 00:05:14.199
We have to ensure her safety first.

00:05:15.079 --> 00:05:16.600
Place her under covert protection.

00:05:17.279 --> 00:05:18.079
Understood.

00:05:19.560 --> 00:05:20.720
But this brother and sister,

00:05:21.120 --> 00:05:22.439
their lives are like a novel,

00:05:23.399 --> 00:05:24.720
bizarre and full of twists.

00:05:28.759 --> 00:05:29.720
Honestly,

00:05:30.560 --> 00:05:32.560
the sick are truly innocent.

00:05:33.439 --> 00:05:34.680
What if it were you?

00:05:35.839 --> 00:05:37.319
If you were Xin Youna's brother,

00:05:38.560 --> 00:05:39.759
would you break the law

00:05:39.920 --> 00:05:41.040
to save her?

00:05:50.040 --> 00:05:51.120
Hello, police.

00:05:51.800 --> 00:05:53.319
We need Xin Youna's medical records,

00:05:53.319 --> 00:05:54.439
and all payment records.

00:05:55.639 --> 00:05:57.360
Can we see Xin Youna right now?

00:05:57.560 --> 00:05:58.439
She's on an IV drip right now.

00:05:58.439 --> 00:05:59.319
You'll have to wait a bit.

00:06:00.480 --> 00:06:01.560
What medication is she on?

00:06:06.079 --> 00:06:06.839
Velipa.

00:06:07.399 --> 00:06:08.759
Velipa.

00:06:11.120 --> 00:06:12.120
Uncle.

00:06:15.120 --> 00:06:16.920
Zhang Heng, what are you doing here?

00:06:17.040 --> 00:06:17.920
Uncle.

00:06:18.199 --> 00:06:19.560
Fancy seeing you here,

00:06:20.199 --> 00:06:21.240
what a coincidence.

00:06:22.160 --> 00:06:23.480
We came to take care of something.

00:06:24.680 --> 00:06:26.879
Transferring Paopao to another hospital?

00:06:28.519 --> 00:06:31.360
It's hard to explain right now.

00:06:31.680 --> 00:06:32.439
Tell you what,

00:06:32.680 --> 00:06:34.279
bring Yaping over for dinner on Sunday.

00:06:34.600 --> 00:06:35.680
Say bye to Uncle.

00:06:36.519 --> 00:06:37.399
Bye, we're heading off.

00:06:37.600 --> 00:06:38.480
Bye-bye, bye-bye.

00:06:41.839 --> 00:06:42.480
Luo Xiao.

00:06:48.800 --> 00:06:50.279
About how long does this need to last?

00:06:50.439 --> 00:06:51.600
Do you have a three-month supply?

00:06:52.160 --> 00:06:52.959
About that.

00:07:05.519 --> 00:07:06.279
Officers,

00:07:06.399 --> 00:07:08.160
these are Xin Youna's medical records.

00:07:12.879 --> 00:07:14.480
Director, can we take these with us?

00:07:15.199 --> 00:07:17.160
We're a private hospital.

00:07:17.600 --> 00:07:19.360
This involves patient privacy.

00:07:20.319 --> 00:07:21.959
If you really need them,

00:07:22.399 --> 00:07:24.439
you'll need a proper subpoena.

00:07:25.399 --> 00:07:27.240
However, within our hospital,

00:07:27.360 --> 00:07:28.279
you're welcome to review them.

00:07:29.519 --> 00:07:30.160
Director,

00:07:30.360 --> 00:07:32.120
have you met Xin Youna's brother?

00:07:32.519 --> 00:07:33.240
Yes.

00:07:34.319 --> 00:07:35.399
He used to come often,

00:07:36.040 --> 00:07:37.279
almost every weekend,

00:07:37.720 --> 00:07:38.839
to visit his sister.

00:07:39.360 --> 00:07:40.319
Every week?

00:07:40.920 --> 00:07:41.519
Yes.

00:07:41.639 --> 00:07:42.560
What's your impression of him?

00:07:43.519 --> 00:07:44.800
He's not very talkative.

00:07:45.120 --> 00:07:46.959
He seems like a reserved person.

00:07:51.920 --> 00:07:53.079
Xin Youna's medical record

00:07:53.079 --> 00:07:54.480
is written in rather complex terms.

00:07:54.639 --> 00:07:56.120
Could you give us a brief

00:07:56.319 --> 00:07:57.240
explanation?

00:07:58.279 --> 00:08:00.199
Sure, let me give a brief overview.

00:08:01.360 --> 00:08:03.319
Xin Youna suffers from

00:08:03.319 --> 00:08:05.000
a rare blood disorder

00:08:05.439 --> 00:08:07.319
called Fanconi anemia.

00:08:07.720 --> 00:08:09.000
People with this disease

00:08:09.120 --> 00:08:10.680
typically face frequent infections

00:08:11.319 --> 00:08:12.959
from a young age,

00:08:13.399 --> 00:08:15.120
and organ deterioration.

00:08:15.879 --> 00:08:17.360
The main thing we can do here

00:08:17.560 --> 00:08:19.519
is provide professional medical care.

00:08:19.959 --> 00:08:21.439
Ideally,

00:08:21.959 --> 00:08:23.680
we can use bone marrow stimulants

00:08:23.839 --> 00:08:26.360
to restore her marrow's blood production.

00:08:27.519 --> 00:08:28.639
Ideally?

00:08:29.160 --> 00:08:29.720
Yes.

00:08:30.240 --> 00:08:33.279
Meaning when finances allow,

00:08:33.600 --> 00:08:34.799
we use imported medication.

00:08:37.360 --> 00:08:38.639
So it's expensive, right?

00:08:39.120 --> 00:08:39.679
Exactly.

00:08:39.759 --> 00:08:41.720
Imported medication is very costly.

00:08:42.960 --> 00:08:44.279
So has her brother

00:08:44.519 --> 00:08:46.000
been covering all these costs?

00:08:47.519 --> 00:08:48.320
As for the costs,

00:08:48.440 --> 00:08:49.759
that's not something we look into.

00:08:49.919 --> 00:08:51.039
We're a hospital.

00:08:51.559 --> 00:08:53.919
We only provide medical services.

00:09:03.080 --> 00:09:04.080
This director...

00:09:04.440 --> 00:09:05.279
Go on.

00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:07.240
When the police showed up at his door,

00:09:07.240 --> 00:09:08.120
asking about a patient,

00:09:08.120 --> 00:09:09.120
he wasn't the least bit surprised.

00:09:09.360 --> 00:09:10.879
He didn't ask why we're investigating her.

00:09:11.360 --> 00:09:13.480
He didn't even glance at her chart.

00:09:13.879 --> 00:09:15.279
He rattled off the details from memory.

00:09:15.840 --> 00:09:16.799
He even clearly remembered her brother,

00:09:16.799 --> 00:09:18.080
how often he came to visit her.

00:09:18.440 --> 00:09:19.440
Doesn't that prove he knows the siblings

00:09:19.440 --> 00:09:20.440
extremely well?

00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:21.759
What else?

00:09:23.799 --> 00:09:25.039
Then there's the nursing home itself.

00:09:25.679 --> 00:09:27.080
Look at how lavish the facilities are.

00:09:27.480 --> 00:09:28.759
The director said it himself,

00:09:29.159 --> 00:09:30.120
imported medication,

00:09:30.759 --> 00:09:31.960
over 10,000 yuan per dose.

00:09:33.120 --> 00:09:34.919
But judging from her bills,

00:09:35.600 --> 00:09:36.240
it looks like with some effort,

00:09:36.240 --> 00:09:38.000
the siblings could afford it, right?

00:09:46.600 --> 00:09:47.799
Fengmao is involved in money laundering.

00:09:48.360 --> 00:09:50.120
Xin Qili was jailed for financial crimes.

00:09:50.559 --> 00:09:52.320
The reason Brother Mao killed Xin Qili

00:09:52.879 --> 00:09:55.080
remains officially unresolved to this day.

00:09:55.519 --> 00:09:56.120
So,

00:09:56.240 --> 00:09:58.000
the real dispute between the two

00:09:59.759 --> 00:10:00.879
is that Xin Qili

00:10:01.080 --> 00:10:02.919
was also involved in Fengmao's laundering.

00:10:03.559 --> 00:10:05.360
That's why we couldn't find a motive.

00:10:11.080 --> 00:10:12.360
That's exactly why

00:10:13.159 --> 00:10:15.840
Xin Youna, upon hearing of his death,

00:10:15.919 --> 00:10:17.200
reacted so indifferently.

00:10:17.720 --> 00:10:19.720
And she strongly resists contact with us.

00:10:21.679 --> 00:10:23.080
I strongly suspect

00:10:23.600 --> 00:10:24.600
that Xin Youna

00:10:24.759 --> 00:10:27.440
knew everything her brother was up to,

00:10:27.759 --> 00:10:30.360
and may have even taken part.

00:10:33.200 --> 00:10:34.559
So what do we do next?

00:10:35.679 --> 00:10:36.440
Hurry up and eat.

00:10:36.559 --> 00:10:37.799
Yaping, don't give her so much.

00:10:37.799 --> 00:10:38.600
She just brushed her teeth.

00:10:38.679 --> 00:10:40.240
She can't have too much fructose.

00:10:41.200 --> 00:10:43.600
Mom, I didn't sneak any.

00:10:43.799 --> 00:10:44.960
You didn't? What's in your mouth? Come.

00:10:45.080 --> 00:10:46.159
Come on, time to study vocab.

00:10:46.919 --> 00:10:47.559
No way.

00:10:50.240 --> 00:10:51.559
Look how spoiled you've made her.

00:10:51.879 --> 00:10:53.399
If you love kids, have your own.

00:10:53.519 --> 00:10:54.559
You're not that young anymore.

00:10:57.200 --> 00:10:58.360
I'm swamped every single day.

00:10:58.480 --> 00:10:59.840
Where would I find time for a kid?

00:11:00.840 --> 00:11:03.240
Didn't you wrap up that debt collection?

00:11:03.879 --> 00:11:04.919
It's far from wrapped up.

00:11:05.080 --> 00:11:06.759
I just have something new on my plate.

00:11:06.879 --> 00:11:08.200
No time for those messy accounts now.

00:11:10.320 --> 00:11:11.080
Yaping,

00:11:12.679 --> 00:11:14.720
our firm's been talking about this lately.

00:11:15.600 --> 00:11:17.720
I hear the government and the banks

00:11:17.799 --> 00:11:19.919
launched a smart manufacturing fund.

00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:20.840
Is that true?

00:11:21.240 --> 00:11:22.559
Yes, that's right. It's true.

00:11:22.879 --> 00:11:24.399
Many projects got approved recently.

00:11:24.840 --> 00:11:27.799
Old factories adding automated lines,

00:11:28.039 --> 00:11:30.039
leasing firms switching to EVs,

00:11:30.279 --> 00:11:31.440
they're all coming to us for loans.

00:11:33.039 --> 00:11:35.320
But I heard that fund was just set up.

00:11:35.960 --> 00:11:37.120
Isn't the approval process

00:11:37.440 --> 00:11:38.519
moving way too fast?

00:11:39.799 --> 00:11:40.639
Normally,

00:11:40.759 --> 00:11:42.039
it'd take three or four months.

00:11:42.320 --> 00:11:43.320
But this time is different.

00:11:43.639 --> 00:11:45.080
It's a government special fund,

00:11:45.200 --> 00:11:46.320
so it goes through a green channel.

00:11:47.440 --> 00:11:49.039
Firms submit materials to us,

00:11:49.240 --> 00:11:50.679
the Commission reviews simultaneously,

00:11:50.960 --> 00:11:52.440
rulings, verifications, subsidy quotas,

00:11:52.759 --> 00:11:53.679
all done in parallel,

00:11:53.799 --> 00:11:55.039
so it gets approved quickly.

00:11:55.919 --> 00:11:57.480
But fast as it is,

00:11:58.200 --> 00:11:59.559
all the work falls on us.

00:12:00.600 --> 00:12:02.360
Contracts, cash flows, purchase lists,

00:12:02.440 --> 00:12:03.519
I have to go through every one.

00:12:04.120 --> 00:12:05.200
Watching the firms by day,

00:12:05.360 --> 00:12:06.440
crunching data at night,

00:12:06.919 --> 00:12:08.200
I can barely straighten my back.

00:12:09.120 --> 00:12:10.480
You really do work hard.

00:12:11.360 --> 00:12:12.200
When did your law firm

00:12:12.200 --> 00:12:13.840
start dealing with investments?

00:12:14.759 --> 00:12:15.399
We don't.

00:12:15.919 --> 00:12:17.080
A client wants to invest,

00:12:17.200 --> 00:12:18.519
so I'm just asking around for him.

00:12:19.679 --> 00:12:20.279
Luo Xiao,

00:12:20.600 --> 00:12:22.399
if your client's legit, send him to me.

00:12:22.559 --> 00:12:23.440
I'm reliable.

00:12:26.879 --> 00:12:28.320
Tech loans.

00:12:33.879 --> 00:12:35.159
This is the overseas money.

00:12:36.279 --> 00:12:36.919
And this

00:12:37.519 --> 00:12:39.720
is our dedicated lending company.

00:12:41.399 --> 00:12:42.279
And this one?

00:12:44.440 --> 00:12:46.840
These are the clean books we show outside.

00:12:48.600 --> 00:12:49.639
Overseas money

00:12:49.759 --> 00:12:52.399
poured into a tech firm with clean books.

00:12:52.600 --> 00:12:53.639
That's perfectly logical.

00:12:54.320 --> 00:12:55.120
Next,

00:12:55.639 --> 00:12:56.759
we turn this dirty bathwater

00:12:57.600 --> 00:12:59.039
into freshly squeezed juice.

00:12:59.759 --> 00:13:00.480
Then,

00:13:00.600 --> 00:13:02.360
apply for a special loan from the bank.

00:13:02.759 --> 00:13:03.440
Finally,

00:13:03.919 --> 00:13:04.840
muddy the waters,

00:13:05.879 --> 00:13:06.840
make the fake pass for real.

00:13:07.519 --> 00:13:09.159
That way we can pump even more money

00:13:09.320 --> 00:13:10.440
into the company,

00:13:11.360 --> 00:13:12.200
and achieve our goal.

00:13:13.639 --> 00:13:14.279
Oh, right.

00:13:15.159 --> 00:13:16.360
After all that,

00:13:16.639 --> 00:13:17.919
we also need someone overseas

00:13:18.039 --> 00:13:19.480
to be our fall guy.

00:13:22.120 --> 00:13:23.440
Who do we get for that, bro?

00:13:25.039 --> 00:13:25.960
How about Young Master Jin?

00:13:37.039 --> 00:13:37.960
Old Luo, about this,

00:13:37.960 --> 00:13:39.639
why didn't you tell me sooner?

00:13:40.720 --> 00:13:42.279
I could've helped you figure it out.

00:13:43.360 --> 00:13:44.600
I mean, our law firm

00:13:45.000 --> 00:13:46.440
investing in the tech industry,

00:13:46.679 --> 00:13:47.960
I never would've dared to imagine it.

00:13:51.159 --> 00:13:52.679
You really kept this hidden.

00:13:53.799 --> 00:13:55.039
Actually, I'd long heard about

00:13:55.120 --> 00:13:57.080
the government's industry support.

00:13:58.159 --> 00:14:00.639
But I didn't expect you to be so sharp.

00:14:00.879 --> 00:14:02.200
You said we'd use our firm's

00:14:02.200 --> 00:14:03.720
credibility as a transitional endorsement.

00:14:04.080 --> 00:14:05.279
That way, for one,

00:14:05.279 --> 00:14:07.200
we can invest openly and legitimately.

00:14:07.480 --> 00:14:08.480
And secondly,

00:14:08.919 --> 00:14:11.440
it'll help attract local investments.

00:14:14.360 --> 00:14:15.320
Old Feng,

00:14:15.919 --> 00:14:17.360
you're pulling my leg now.

00:14:17.759 --> 00:14:19.600
I'm just trying to get through the review,

00:14:19.679 --> 00:14:21.279
adding a little support.

00:14:23.559 --> 00:14:24.840
You know, I've been thinking,

00:14:26.200 --> 00:14:26.840
back in our school days,

00:14:26.840 --> 00:14:28.399
you used to say one thing to me.

00:14:29.840 --> 00:14:31.320
You said choices matter more than effort.

00:14:32.639 --> 00:14:33.480
You said,

00:14:33.799 --> 00:14:35.279
us grinding through case after case,

00:14:35.279 --> 00:14:36.919
when's it ever going to end?

00:14:38.320 --> 00:14:40.120
If we pull this one off,

00:14:41.360 --> 00:14:42.840
wouldn't we be set for life?

00:14:45.639 --> 00:14:47.000
I'll put in some personally too.

00:14:48.240 --> 00:14:49.519
Add my name to it.

00:14:53.720 --> 00:14:54.679
Old Feng,

00:14:56.200 --> 00:14:57.960
it's not that I won't let you invest.

00:14:58.279 --> 00:14:59.360
I'm just the middleman here.

00:14:59.440 --> 00:15:00.600
Whether you can be listed on the project,

00:15:00.600 --> 00:15:01.679
it's not up to me.

00:15:02.360 --> 00:15:03.120
Old classmate,

00:15:03.200 --> 00:15:05.320
what are you saying? Not up to you?

00:15:08.159 --> 00:15:09.639
I'm telling you, this is settled.

00:15:09.840 --> 00:15:10.519
I'm putting in the money.

00:15:10.799 --> 00:15:11.519
It's decided.

00:15:12.840 --> 00:15:13.600
Mr. Liu,

00:15:14.879 --> 00:15:16.279
I know, you...

00:15:17.159 --> 00:15:17.919
Okay, okay, okay.